    <div class="abstract">
      <div class="block-title">Abstract</div>
      <p>This report analyzes the evolution of the global film industry from 1990 to 2025, exploring trends in genres, budgets, duration, and geographical production centers. Through an exploratory data analysis of a comprehensive IMDb dataset, we uncover key shifts in public taste and industry economics. Findings indicate a rise in action and thriller genres, a steady increase in production budgets, and a growing average film duration. Notably, the analysis reveals a very weak correlation between a film’s budget and its audience rating, suggesting that storytelling quality remains more critical than financial investment. The United States continues to dominate production, but cinematic excellence is a global phenomenon, with significant contributions from countries like the UK, Japan, and India.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
