<section id="q2-how-have-movie-budgets-evolved-over-time" class="level2" data-number="3.2">
<h2 data-number="3.2"><span class="header-section-number">3.2</span> Q2: How have movie budgets evolved over time?</h2>
<p>To examine how the economics of filmmaking have changed, we analyze the median movie budget per year from 1990 to 2025. Using the median instead of the mean reduces the influence of extremely high-budget “tentpole” productions, allowing us to observe general industry trends more accurately. We also adjust for inflation.</p>
<p><strong>Data Source for Inflation:</strong> U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics (CPI-U).</p>
<div id="cell-fig-budget-evolution" class="cell" data-execution_count="3">
<details class="code-fold">
<summary>Code</summary>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb2"><pre class="sourceCode python cell-code"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb2-1"><a href="#cb2-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># CPI data (Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers) sourced from U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics</span></span>
<span id="cb2-2"><a href="#cb2-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Base year for adjustment: 2025 (using estimated CPI)</span></span>
<span id="cb2-3"><a href="#cb2-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cpi_data <span class="op">=</span> {</span>
<span id="cb2-4"><a href="#cb2-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">1990</span>: <span class="fl">130.7</span>, <span class="dv">1991</span>: <span class="fl">136.2</span>, <span class="dv">1992</span>: <span class="fl">140.3</span>, <span class="dv">1993</span>: <span class="fl">144.5</span>, <span class="dv">1994</span>: <span class="fl">148.2</span>,</span>
<span id="cb2-5"><a href="#cb2-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">1995</span>: <span class="fl">152.4</span>, <span class="dv">1996</span>: <span class="fl">156.9</span>, <span class="dv">1997</span>: <span class="fl">160.5</span>, <span class="dv">1998</span>: <span class="fl">163.0</span>, <span class="dv">1999</span>: <span class="fl">166.6</span>,</span>
<span id="cb2-6"><a href="#cb2-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">2000</span>: <span class="fl">172.2</span>, <span class="dv">2001</span>: <span class="fl">177.1</span>, <span class="dv">2002</span>: <span class="fl">179.9</span>, <span class="dv">2003</span>: <span class="fl">184.0</span>, <span class="dv">2004</span>: <span class="fl">188.9</span>,</span>
<span id="cb2-7"><a href="#cb2-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">2005</span>: <span class="fl">195.3</span>, <span class="dv">2006</span>: <span class="fl">201.6</span>, <span class="dv">2007</span>: <span class="fl">207.3</span>, <span class="dv">2008</span>: <span class="fl">215.3</span>, <span class="dv">2009</span>: <span class="fl">214.5</span>,</span>
<span id="cb2-8"><a href="#cb2-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">2010</span>: <span class="fl">218.1</span>, <span class="dv">2011</span>: <span class="fl">224.9</span>, <span class="dv">2012</span>: <span class="fl">229.6</span>, <span class="dv">2013</span>: <span class="fl">233.0</span>, <span class="dv">2014</span>: <span class="fl">236.7</span>,</span>
<span id="cb2-9"><a href="#cb2-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">2015</span>: <span class="fl">237.0</span>, <span class="dv">2016</span>: <span class="fl">240.0</span>, <span class="dv">2017</span>: <span class="fl">245.1</span>, <span class="dv">2018</span>: <span class="fl">251.1</span>, <span class="dv">2019</span>: <span class="fl">255.7</span>,</span>
<span id="cb2-10"><a href="#cb2-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">2020</span>: <span class="fl">258.8</span>, <span class="dv">2021</span>: <span class="fl">271.0</span>, <span class="dv">2022</span>: <span class="fl">292.7</span>, <span class="dv">2023</span>: <span class="fl">304.7</span>, <span class="dv">2024</span>: <span class="fl">314.0</span>,</span>
<span id="cb2-11"><a href="#cb2-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="dv">2025</span>: <span class="fl">322.0</span></span>
<span id="cb2-12"><a href="#cb2-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>}</span>
<span id="cb2-13"><a href="#cb2-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-14"><a href="#cb2-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="kw">def</span> adjust_for_inflation(row):</span>
<span id="cb2-15"><a href="#cb2-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    year <span class="op">=</span> row[<span class="st">&#39;release_date&#39;</span>].year</span>
<span id="cb2-16"><a href="#cb2-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">if</span> year <span class="kw">in</span> cpi_data:</span>
<span id="cb2-17"><a href="#cb2-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">return</span> row[<span class="st">&#39;budget&#39;</span>] <span class="op">*</span> (cpi_data[<span class="dv">2025</span>] <span class="op">/</span> cpi_data[year])</span>
<span id="cb2-18"><a href="#cb2-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">return</span> row[<span class="st">&#39;budget&#39;</span>]</span>
<span id="cb2-19"><a href="#cb2-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-20"><a href="#cb2-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Apply inflation adjustment to the main dataframe</span></span>
<span id="cb2-21"><a href="#cb2-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data[<span class="st">&#39;budget_adjusted&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> data.<span class="bu">apply</span>(adjust_for_inflation, axis<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">1</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-22"><a href="#cb2-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-23"><a href="#cb2-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Calculate median nominal and adjusted budget per year</span></span>
<span id="cb2-24"><a href="#cb2-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>budget_evolution <span class="op">=</span> data.groupby(data[<span class="st">&#39;release_date&#39;</span>].dt.year)[[<span class="st">&#39;budget&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;budget_adjusted&#39;</span>]].median().reset_index()</span>
<span id="cb2-25"><a href="#cb2-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>budget_evolution.columns <span class="op">=</span> [<span class="st">&#39;year&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;Nominal Budget&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;Real Budget (2025 USD)&#39;</span>]</span>
<span id="cb2-26"><a href="#cb2-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-27"><a href="#cb2-27" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Melt for plotting</span></span>
<span id="cb2-28"><a href="#cb2-28" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>budget_evolution_melted <span class="op">=</span> budget_evolution.melt(<span class="st">&#39;year&#39;</span>, var_name<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;Budget Type&#39;</span>, value_name<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;Amount&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-29"><a href="#cb2-29" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-30"><a href="#cb2-30" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Create the plot</span></span>
<span id="cb2-31"><a href="#cb2-31" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>fig, ax <span class="op">=</span> plt.subplots(figsize<span class="op">=</span>(<span class="fl">8.25</span>, <span class="fl">4.5</span>))</span>
<span id="cb2-32"><a href="#cb2-32" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
