Figure 2: Median movie production budget: Nominal vs. Inflation-Adjusted (Base 2025)
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Interpretation:</strong></p>
<p><a href="#fig-budget-evolution" class="quarto-xref">Figure 8</a> reveals a surprising divergence between nominal spending and real purchasing power. While the nominal budget (purple line) suggests a gradual increase from roughly $11 million in 1990 to peaks of $30 million in recent years, the inflation-adjusted “Real Budget” (gold line, Base 2025) tells a starkly different story. Contrary to the expectation that costs have skyrocketed, the regression line indicates a clear downward trend in real median budgets over the 35-year period.</p>
<p>In real terms (2025 dollars), median budgets actually peaked in the late 1990s, reaching highs of over $35 million. Since then, despite significant volatility, the purchasing power allocated to the median film has steadily eroded, dropping to approximately $19 million by 2025.</p>
<p>Several factors may explain this real-term decline. First, the democratization of digital filmmaking tools may have lowered the barrier to entry, allowing more low-to-mid-budget films to be produced more cheaply. Second, the industry may be experiencing a “hollowing out” effect: while massive blockbusters (not captured by the median) have ballooned in cost, the “middle-class” movie has faced tightening budget constraints.</p>
<p>The graph also highlights distinct periods of volatility. A sharp dip is visible around the 2008 financial crisis and again in the mid-2010s. Interestingly, while there was a significant spike in real spending around 2022–2023 (likely a post-pandemic production surge) values have since corrected downward. Overall, the analysis overturns the assumption that filmmaking is becoming universally more expensive; instead, it suggests that outside of mega-blockbusters, the typical film is being made with a leaner real-world budget than it was three decades ago.</p>
</section>
<section id="q3-to-what-extent-does-financial-investment-budget-influence-audience-reception-imdb-rating" class="level2" data-number="3.3">
<h2 data-number="3.3"><span class="header-section-number">3.3</span> Q3: To what extent does financial investment (budget) influence audience reception (IMDb rating)?</h2>
<p>A central question for any film producer is whether more money leads to a better movie. We investigate this by plotting <strong>inflation-adjusted budgets</strong> against their IMDb ratings. Given that budgets span several orders of magnitude, we use a logarithmic scale for the budget axis to better visualize the relationship.</p>
<div id="cell-fig-budget-rating-correlation" class="cell" data-execution_count="4">
<details class="code-fold">
<summary>Code</summary>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb3"><pre class="sourceCode python cell-code"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb3-1"><a href="#cb3-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Filter out rows with missing budget or rating for this analysis</span></span>
<span id="cb3-2"><a href="#cb3-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>budget_rating_data <span class="op">=</span> data.dropna(subset<span class="op">=</span>[<span class="st">&#39;budget_adjusted&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;rating&#39;</span>])</span>
<span id="cb3-3"><a href="#cb3-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-4"><a href="#cb3-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Create the plot</span></span>
<span id="cb3-5"><a href="#cb3-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>fig, ax <span class="op">=</span> plt.subplots(figsize<span class="op">=</span>(<span class="fl">8.25</span>, <span class="fl">5.25</span>))</span>
<span id="cb3-6"><a href="#cb3-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-7"><a href="#cb3-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>sns.regplot(data<span class="op">=</span>budget_rating_data, x<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;budget_adjusted&#39;</span>, y<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;rating&#39;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb3-8"><a href="#cb3-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>            ax<span class="op">=</span>ax, scatter_kws<span class="op">=</span>{<span class="st">&#39;alpha&#39;</span>: <span class="fl">0.2</span>, <span class="st">&#39;s&#39;</span>: <span class="dv">20</span>},</span>
<span id="cb3-9"><a href="#cb3-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>            line_kws<span class="op">=</span>{<span class="st">&#39;color&#39;</span>: <span class="st">&#39;red&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;linewidth&#39;</span>: <span class="dv">2</span>})</span>
<span id="cb3-10"><a href="#cb3-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-11"><a href="#cb3-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Customize plot</span></span>
<span id="cb3-12"><a href="#cb3-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_xscale(<span class="st">&#39;log&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-13"><a href="#cb3-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_title(<span class="st">&quot;Correlation Between Real Budget and IMDb Rating&quot;</span>, </span>
<span id="cb3-14"><a href="#cb3-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">16</span>, fontweight<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;bold&#39;</span>, pad<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">15</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-15"><a href="#cb3-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_xlabel(<span class="st">&quot;Budget (Inflation Adjusted to 2025 USD, log scale)&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-16"><a href="#cb3-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_ylabel(<span class="st">&quot;IMDb Rating&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-17"><a href="#cb3-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.grid(<span class="va">True</span>, alpha<span class="op">=</span><span class="fl">0.3</span>, linestyle<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;--&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-18"><a href="#cb3-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-19"><a href="#cb3-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Add correlation coefficient</span></span>
<span id="cb3-20"><a href="#cb3-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>correlation <span class="op">=</span> budget_rating_data[<span class="st">&#39;budget_adjusted&#39;</span>].corr(budget_rating_data[<span class="st">&#39;rating&#39;</span>])</span>
<span id="cb3-21"><a href="#cb3-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.text(<span class="fl">0.05</span>, <span class="fl">0.95</span>, <span class="ss">f&#39;Pearson Correlation: </span><span class="sc">{</span>correlation<span class="sc">:.3f}</span><span class="ss">&#39;</span>, </span>
<span id="cb3-22"><a href="#cb3-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        transform<span class="op">=</span>ax.transAxes, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">11</span>,</span>
