<span id="cb10-397"><a href="#cb10-397" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_title(<span class="st">&quot;Correlation Between Real Budget and Worldwide Gross Revenue&quot;</span>, </span>
<span id="cb10-398"><a href="#cb10-398" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">16</span>, fontweight<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;bold&#39;</span>, pad<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">15</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-399"><a href="#cb10-399" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_xlabel(<span class="st">&quot;Budget (Inflation Adjusted to 2025 USD, log scale)&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-400"><a href="#cb10-400" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_ylabel(<span class="st">&quot;Worldwide Gross (Inflation Adjusted to 2025 USD, log scale)&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-401"><a href="#cb10-401" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.grid(<span class="va">True</span>, alpha<span class="op">=</span><span class="fl">0.3</span>, linestyle<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;--&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-402"><a href="#cb10-402" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-403"><a href="#cb10-403" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Add correlation coefficient</span></span>
<span id="cb10-404"><a href="#cb10-404" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>correlation_revenue <span class="op">=</span> budget_revenue_data[<span class="st">&#39;budget_adjusted&#39;</span>].corr(budget_revenue_data[<span class="st">&#39;gross_adjusted&#39;</span>])</span>
<span id="cb10-405"><a href="#cb10-405" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.text(<span class="fl">0.05</span>, <span class="fl">0.95</span>, <span class="ss">f&#39;Pearson Correlation: </span><span class="sc">{</span>correlation_revenue<span class="sc">:.3f}</span><span class="ss">&#39;</span>, </span>
<span id="cb10-406"><a href="#cb10-406" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        transform<span class="op">=</span>ax.transAxes, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">11</span>,</span>
<span id="cb10-407"><a href="#cb10-407" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        verticalalignment<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;top&#39;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb10-408"><a href="#cb10-408" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        bbox<span class="op">=</span><span class="bu">dict</span>(boxstyle<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;round&#39;</span>, facecolor<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;wheat&#39;</span>, alpha<span class="op">=</span><span class="fl">0.5</span>))</span>
<span id="cb10-409"><a href="#cb10-409" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-410"><a href="#cb10-410" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.legend(loc<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;lower right&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-411"><a href="#cb10-411" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>plt.tight_layout()</span>
<span id="cb10-412"><a href="#cb10-412" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>plt.show()</span>
<span id="cb10-413"><a href="#cb10-413" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span>
<span id="cb10-414"><a href="#cb10-414" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-415"><a href="#cb10-415" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>**Interpretation:**</span>
<span id="cb10-416"><a href="#cb10-416" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-417"><a href="#cb10-417" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>@fig-budget-revenue-correlation reveals a **strong positive correlation** between a film&#39;s inflation-adjusted budget and its worldwide gross revenue, with a Pearson correlation coefficient of approximately 0.70–0.75. This stands in stark contrast to the near-zero correlation observed between budget and IMDb rating in the previous section.</span>
<span id="cb10-418"><a href="#cb10-418" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-419"><a href="#cb10-419" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>Several key observations emerge from this analysis:</span>
<span id="cb10-420"><a href="#cb10-420" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-421"><a href="#cb10-421" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="ss">1. </span>**Strong Linear Relationship**: The upward-sloping regression line (red) demonstrates that, on average, films with higher budgets tend to generate higher box office revenues. This relationship is visually apparent and statistically significant.</span>
<span id="cb10-422"><a href="#cb10-422" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-423"><a href="#cb10-423" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="ss">2. </span>**Break-Even Analysis**: The black dashed line represents the break-even point where gross revenue equals the production budget. Most data points cluster above this line, indicating that the majority of films in our dataset recouped their production costs at the box office. However, it&#39;s important to note that this does not account for marketing costs (often 50-100% of the production budget) or distribution fees, meaning true profitability is harder to determine.</span>
<span id="cb10-424"><a href="#cb10-424" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-425"><a href="#cb10-425" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="ss">3. </span>**Variance at Higher Budgets**: While the correlation is strong, there is considerable variance, especially at higher budget levels. Some high-budget films ($100M+) achieve extraordinary returns (appearing well above the regression line), while others underperform relative to their investment. This variance reflects the inherent risk in blockbuster filmmaking—while big budgets can lead to big returns, they can also result in significant losses.</span>
<span id="cb10-426"><a href="#cb10-426" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-427"><a href="#cb10-427" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="ss">4. </span>**Low-Budget Outliers**: Several low-budget films (below $10M) show remarkable returns, appearing far above the break-even line. These represent the &quot;indie success stories&quot;—films that achieved commercial success disproportionate to their modest investments, often through word-of-mouth, critical acclaim, or viral marketing.</span>
<span id="cb10-428"><a href="#cb10-428" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-429"><a href="#cb10-429" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>**Key Takeaway**: While money cannot buy audience appreciation (as shown in Q3), it does correlate strongly with commercial performance. This makes intuitive sense: larger budgets enable wider theatrical releases, more extensive marketing campaigns, bigger stars, and higher production values that attract audiences to theaters. However, the scatter around the trend line reminds us that financial success is never guaranteed—storytelling, timing, and market conditions all play crucial roles.</span>
<span id="cb10-430"><a href="#cb10-430" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-431"><a href="#cb10-431" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">## Q4: How has the typical duration of feature films evolved over the last three decades?</span></span>
<span id="cb10-432"><a href="#cb10-432" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-433"><a href="#cb10-433" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>Have you ever felt that movies are getting longer? This analysis investigates whether there is data to support this common perception. We plot the average movie duration per year to see if a trend emerges.</span>
<span id="cb10-434"><a href="#cb10-434" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-435"><a href="#cb10-435" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>quarto-executable-code-5450563D</span>
<span id="cb10-436"><a href="#cb10-436" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-437"><a href="#cb10-437" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```python</span></span>
<span id="cb10-438"><a href="#cb10-438" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#| label: fig-duration-evolution</span></span>
<span id="cb10-439"><a href="#cb10-439" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#| fig-cap: &quot;Average movie duration (in minutes) from 1990 to 2025&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb10-440"><a href="#cb10-440" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-441"><a href="#cb10-441" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Calculate average duration per year</span></span>
<span id="cb10-442"><a href="#cb10-442" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>avg_duration_per_year <span class="op">=</span> data.groupby(data[<span class="st">&#39;release_date&#39;</span>].dt.year)[<span class="st">&#39;duration_minutes&#39;</span>].mean().reset_index()</span>
<span id="cb10-443"><a href="#cb10-443" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>avg_duration_per_year.columns <span class="op">=</span> [<span class="st">&#39;year&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;avg_duration&#39;</span>]</span>
<span id="cb10-444"><a href="#cb10-444" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-445"><a href="#cb10-445" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Create the plot</span></span>
<span id="cb10-446"><a href="#cb10-446" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>fig, ax <span class="op">=</span> plt.subplots(figsize<span class="op">=</span>(<span class="fl">8.25</span>, <span class="fl">4.5</span>))</span>
<span id="cb10-447"><a href="#cb10-447" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-448"><a href="#cb10-448" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>sns.lineplot(data<span class="op">=</span>avg_duration_per_year, x<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;year&#39;</span>, y<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;avg_duration&#39;</span>, ax<span class="op">=</span>ax, marker<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;.&#39;</span>, color<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;darkgreen&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-449"><a href="#cb10-449" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-450"><a href="#cb10-450" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Add a trend line to show the overall increase</span></span>
<span id="cb10-451"><a href="#cb10-451" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>sns.regplot(data<span class="op">=</span>avg_duration_per_year, x<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;year&#39;</span>, y<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;avg_duration&#39;</span>, ax<span class="op">=</span>ax, scatter<span class="op">=</span><span class="va">False</span>, color<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;red&#39;</span>, line_kws<span class="op">=</span>{<span class="st">&#39;linestyle&#39;</span>:<span class="st">&#39;--&#39;</span>})</span>
<span id="cb10-452"><a href="#cb10-452" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-453"><a href="#cb10-453" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Customize plot</span></span>
<span id="cb10-454"><a href="#cb10-454" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_title(<span class="st">&quot;Average Movie Duration Evolution (1990-2025)&quot;</span>, </span>
<span id="cb10-455"><a href="#cb10-455" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">16</span>, fontweight<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;bold&#39;</span>, pad<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">15</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-456"><a href="#cb10-456" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_xlabel(<span class="st">&quot;Year&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-457"><a href="#cb10-457" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_ylabel(<span class="st">&quot;Average Duration (minutes)&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-458"><a href="#cb10-458" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.grid(<span class="va">True</span>, alpha<span class="op">=</span><span class="fl">0.5</span>, linestyle<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;--&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-459"><a href="#cb10-459" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-460"><a href="#cb10-460" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>plt.tight_layout()</span>
<span id="cb10-461"><a href="#cb10-461" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>plt.show()</span>
<span id="cb10-462"><a href="#cb10-462" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span>
<span id="cb10-463"><a href="#cb10-463" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-464"><a href="#cb10-464" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>**Interpretation:**</span>
<span id="cb10-465"><a href="#cb10-465" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-466"><a href="#cb10-466" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>@fig-duration-evolution shows that the average duration of films has gradually increased over the last 3 decades. While films averaged around 102–104 minutes in the early 1990s, in recent years the average has more frequently reached 106–108 minutes, with some peaks even higher.</span>
<span id="cb10-467"><a href="#cb10-467" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-468"><a href="#cb10-468" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>A notable exception emerges between approximately 2004 and 2012, during which time the average runtime decreases by several minutes compared to preceding and subsequent periods. This decline could be due to a number of factors, such as the increased popularity of mid-budget commercial comedies and action films, which tend to be shorter, as well as increased studio pressure to reduce runtimes in order to fit in more daily theatrical showings. There was also a shift towards faster-paced storytelling during the early 2000s. There were also fewer very long &#39;epic-style&#39; releases during this period than in the later 2010s, which may have contributed to the lower averages.</span>
<span id="cb10-469"><a href="#cb10-469" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-470"><a href="#cb10-470" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>Although there are yearly fluctuations, likely due to changes in sample size or variations in genre popularity, the overall regression trend line confirms a steady increase throughout the period.</span>
<span id="cb10-471"><a href="#cb10-471" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-472"><a href="#cb10-472" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>This rise is modest rather than dramatic, but it is consistent, indicating that films today are generally a few minutes longer than those produced in the 1990s. This shift may reflect broader industry trends, such as the growth of franchise-based &#39;event movies&#39;, which often have longer narratives. The expansion of streaming platforms may also be a contributing factor: without the physical constraints imposed by VHS, DVDs or theatrical scheduling, filmmakers have greater freedom to determine runtime.</span>
<span id="cb10-473"><a href="#cb10-473" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-474"><a href="#cb10-474" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>Overall, the data supports the idea that films have become slightly longer over time. While the increase is not extreme, it signals a shift in storytelling practices, with modern productions tending to embrace more complex or expansive narratives than in previous decades.</span>
<span id="cb10-475"><a href="#cb10-475" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-476"><a href="#cb10-476" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">## Q5: Which countries have dominated global film production?</span></span>
<span id="cb10-477"><a href="#cb10-477" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-478"><a href="#cb10-478" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>To understand the geographical landscape of the film industry, we identify the top movie-producing countries for each decade (from the 1990s to the 2020s). This helps reveal the centers of film production and how their influence has evolved.</span>
<span id="cb10-479"><a href="#cb10-479" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-480"><a href="#cb10-480" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>quarto-executable-code-5450563D</span>
<span id="cb10-481"><a href="#cb10-481" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-482"><a href="#cb10-482" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```python</span></span>
<span id="cb10-483"><a href="#cb10-483" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#| label: fig-country-production</span></span>
<span id="cb10-484"><a href="#cb10-484" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#| fig-cap: &quot;Top 5 movie-producing countries by decade&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb10-485"><a href="#cb10-485" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-486"><a href="#cb10-486" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># The &#39;countries_origin&#39; is a string representation of a list. We need to parse it.</span></span>
<span id="cb10-487"><a href="#cb10-487" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># We&#39;ll take the first country as the primary country of origin.</span></span>
<span id="cb10-488"><a href="#cb10-488" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="kw">def</span> get_first_country(countries_str):</span>
<span id="cb10-489"><a href="#cb10-489" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">if</span> pd.isna(countries_str):</span>
<span id="cb10-490"><a href="#cb10-490" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">return</span> <span class="va">None</span></span>
<span id="cb10-491"><a href="#cb10-491" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">try</span>:</span>
<span id="cb10-492"><a href="#cb10-492" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        countries_list <span class="op">=</span> ast.literal_eval(countries_str)</span>
<span id="cb10-493"><a href="#cb10-493" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">if</span> countries_list:</span>
<span id="cb10-494"><a href="#cb10-494" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>            <span class="cf">return</span> countries_list[<span class="dv">0</span>]</span>
<span id="cb10-495"><a href="#cb10-495" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">except</span> (<span class="pp">ValueError</span>, <span class="pp">SyntaxError</span>):</span>
<span id="cb10-496"><a href="#cb10-496" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">return</span> <span class="va">None</span></span>
<span id="cb10-497"><a href="#cb10-497" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">return</span> <span class="va">None</span></span>
<span id="cb10-498"><a href="#cb10-498" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-499"><a href="#cb10-499" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data[<span class="st">&#39;primary_country&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> data[<span class="st">&#39;countries_origin&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(get_first_country)</span>
<span id="cb10-500"><a href="#cb10-500" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-501"><a href="#cb10-501" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Get the top 5 countries per decade</span></span>
<span id="cb10-502"><a href="#cb10-502" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>top_countries_per_decade <span class="op">=</span> (</span>
<span id="cb10-503"><a href="#cb10-503" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    data.dropna(subset<span class="op">=</span>[<span class="st">&#39;primary_country&#39;</span>])</span>
<span id="cb10-504"><a href="#cb10-504" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    .groupby([<span class="st">&#39;decade&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;primary_country&#39;</span>])</span>
<span id="cb10-505"><a href="#cb10-505" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    .size()</span>
<span id="cb10-506"><a href="#cb10-506" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    .reset_index(name<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;count&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-507"><a href="#cb10-507" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    .groupby(<span class="st">&#39;decade&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-508"><a href="#cb10-508" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    .<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: x.nlargest(<span class="dv">5</span>, <span class="st">&#39;count&#39;</span>))</span>
<span id="cb10-509"><a href="#cb10-509" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    .reset_index(drop<span class="op">=</span><span class="va">True</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-510"><a href="#cb10-510" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>)</span>
<span id="cb10-511"><a href="#cb10-511" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-512"><a href="#cb10-512" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Create the plot</span></span>
<span id="cb10-513"><a href="#cb10-513" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>fig, ax <span class="op">=</span> plt.subplots(figsize<span class="op">=</span>(<span class="fl">8.25</span>, <span class="fl">5.25</span>))</span>
<span id="cb10-514"><a href="#cb10-514" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-515"><a href="#cb10-515" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>sns.barplot(data<span class="op">=</span>top_countries_per_decade, x<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;decade&#39;</span>, y<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;count&#39;</span>, hue<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;primary_country&#39;</span>, ax<span class="op">=</span>ax, palette<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;viridis&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-516"><a href="#cb10-516" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb10-517"><a href="#cb10-517" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Customize plot</span></span>
<span id="cb10-518"><a href="#cb10-518" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_title(<span class="st">&quot;Top Movie-Producing Countries by Decade&quot;</span>, </span>
<span id="cb10-519"><a href="#cb10-519" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">16</span>, fontweight<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;bold&#39;</span>, pad<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">15</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-520"><a href="#cb10-520" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_xlabel(<span class="st">&quot;Decade&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-521"><a href="#cb10-521" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.set_ylabel(<span class="st">&quot;Number of Movies Produced&quot;</span>, fontsize<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">12</span>)</span>
<span id="cb10-522"><a href="#cb10-522" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>ax.legend(title<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;Country&#39;</span>, bbox_to_anchor<span class="op">=</span>(<span class="fl">1.05</span>, <span class="dv">1</span>), loc<span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&#39;upper left&#39;</span>)</span>
